    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nBecause `IncSearch` and `Substitute` have lower priority than any `Diff` highlight when using `:s`, it is hard or sometimes even impossible to see the strings that you are replacing.\nPriority to 0.12, `Diff` has lower priority than `IncSearch` and `Substitute`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -d new old` where `new` and `old` are too files with some differences.\n2. `:%s/pattern/substitue`\n3. Observe that `pattern` is only highlighted on lines without changes, and completely masked by `Diff` highlight on any changed lines.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`pattern` should be highlighted everywhere.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
