            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "So I looked into this myself and found that this is actually a lot more difficult than I thought.\n\nIt turns out, `hl-Substitute` is implemented using extmark, whereas search/diff are native highlighting.\n\nIn `drawline.c`\n\nFirst, `extmark_attr` is computed on line 1857. Then, `diff_hlf` is computed and applied to `line_attr`. Next, `char_attr_pri` (character attribute primary) is set to the line attribute or the line plus search attribute. This is what allows the search highlight to be drawn on top of diff highlight.\n\n`extmark_attr` is not used until line 2234-2240 where it is combined as a low priority attribute.\n\nOne \"obvious fix\" is to add\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/drawline.c b/src/nvim/drawline.c\nindex d2f9f17cc0..caadbe8229 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/drawline.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/drawline.c\n@@ -1959,6 +1959,8 @@ int win_line(win_T *wp, linenr_T lnum, int startrow, int endrow, int col_rows, b\n         }\n       } else if (search_attr != 0) {\n         char_attr_pri = hl_combine_attr(wlv.line_attr, search_attr);\n+      } else if (extmark_attr != 0) {\n+        char_attr_pri = hl_combine_attr(wlv.line_attr, extmark_attr);\n       } else if (wlv.line_attr != 0\n                  && ((wlv.fromcol == -10 && wlv.tocol == MAXCOL)\n                      || wlv.vcol < wlv.fromcol\n```\n\nBut that makes all extmarks take priority over `Diff` and `CursorLine`, which is certainly not desirable.\n\nSome possible solutions I can come up with:\n1. Allow an extmark to be flagged as super high priority (either adding a new dedicated flag or set a threshold for the current `priority` field).\n2. Consider the extmark as important if bg is set.\n3. (Rework `drawline.c:win_line` so everything uses the same priority system).\n\nPS. The reason why vim doesn't have this problem is because vim `:s` doesn't support drawing the replacement using virtual text, and therefore able to just highlight pattern as `IncSearch`",
